{
  "text": "Both the bootstrap and SE measures demonstrate that there is no increased spread of values during the MWP (Fig. 1) . SE is actually largest during recent decadesthis is at least partly related to diverging trends in late 20th century tree-ring records [CITATION_1] ). This quantification of proxy data coherence suggests that it was erroneous to conclude that the records displayed in AR4 are indicative for a heterogeneous climate during the MWP. ",
